Assignment name  : epur_str
Expected files   : epur_str.c
Allowed functions: write
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Write a program that takes a string, and displays this string with exactly one
space between words, with no spaces or tabs at the beginning or the end.

A "word" is a part of the string separated by spaces or tabs.

The result must be followed by a newline.

If the number of parameters is not 1, the program displays only a newline.

Examples:

$> ./epur_str "See? It's easy to print the same thing" | cat -e
See? It's easy to print the same thing$

$> ./epur_str " this        time it      will     be    more complex  " | cat -e
this time it will be more complex$

$> ./epur_str "No S*** Sherlock..." | cat -e
No S*** Sherlock...$

$> ./epur_str "   " | cat -e
$

$> ./epur_str | cat -e
$
